> What is the best way to find out if there is an enum for a string? Maybe it is the simplest to run analysis.rb on a conv.py output.

What you propose works and is probably cleaner. `conv.py` does something really crude [using the schema](https://github.com/achamayou/draft-chamayou-cospdx/blob/main/conv/conv.py#L29):

```
        for line in schema_path.read_text().splitlines():
            line = line.strip()
            ...
            elif line.startswith("const."):
                const, value = line[len("const.") :].split("=")
                self.consts[const.strip()] = value.strip()

...
    if isinstance(value, str):
        if value in schema.consts:
            return schema.consts[value]
```
